The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, Dec. 6: The Indian Drug Manufacturers Association (Idma) has demanded a price increase of 20 per cent for all scheduled formulations because of the rise in the procurement cost of bulk drugs and packaging materials. The pharma industry has urged the government to ease the pressure on it to ensure that manufacturers are able to continue providing quality medicines to the public, Idma said in a statement.                            
	 New Delhi, Dec. 6: Kingfisher Airlines has reduced fuel surcharge on air tickets that will bring down fares by up to Rs 400 on all domestic routes. The cut will be applicable with immediate effect, a company spokesperson said. Thus, travelling by Kingfisher Red will see a cut of up to Rs 300 on routes of up to 750 kilometres to Rs 1,950.                            
	 Mumbai, Dec. 6: Mahindra amp; Mahindra will shut down its five manufacturing plants at Nasik, Kandivli, Igatpuri, Zaheerabad and Haridwar for three to six days this month. The plants will work partially during the month, M amp;M said.                                                                                                                         
